					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5993619#post-3812874</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5993619/scp-3830#post-3812874</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 25 May 2018 16:54:05 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TheShrike</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1834351</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>seemingly resembling a betta fish</p> </blockquote> <p>Doesn't really make sense. It either resembles a betta fish or it doesn't. &quot;Seemingly&quot; would only be appropriate if there is a chance that the doll has some camouflage, and doesn't actually look like a betta fish. If there's argument over whether it actually resembles a betta fish, then the word you want is &quot;arguably&quot;.</p> <p>Edit: also, fixed a typo</p> <p>And, also, -1 is used but never assigned. It clearly refers to the dream state, but that isn't actually stated anywhere.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
